==English==

===Etymology===
[[time]] + [[is]] + [[of the essence]]

===Idiom===
'''[[time]] [[is]] [[of]] [[the]] [[essence]]'''

# Used to express a need for [[haste]] in action or response.  
# Said when something must be done [[immediately]]: When transporting organs for transplant, time is of the essence.
# {{law}} When used in a [[contract]], places the other party on notice that failure to complete a required performance by a [[date certain]] set forth therein will constitute an [[incurable]] [[breach]].

